- Hello. 
 - Hi.

76
00:08:01,730 --> 00:08:03,370
Teacher Son.

77
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:08,550
- I have— 
 - I need to get going. I'm sorry!

78
00:08:08,550 --> 00:08:12,250
What? Wait, Teacher Son!

79
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,820
Wait...

80
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:42,960
I saw him going this way.

81
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,850
Didn't he?

82
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:04,460
   

83
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,120
You scared me!

84
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:29,610
You should have called out if you were here. What are you doing?

85
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:30,890
I did call you.

86
00:09:30,890 --> 00:09:32,410
Did you really?

87
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:35,260
Was I too focused again?

88
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:38,040
Hey, give me some goggles, too.

89
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:40,270
Don't bother me; go away.

90
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:45,430
Do you know how delicate a prepping operation is?

91
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:49,970
No, I need to keep myself busy.

92
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:51,300
Hey!

93
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,090
What?

94
00:10:14,950 --> 00:10:16,970
Stop peeling.

95
00:10:16,970 --> 00:10:19,700
This isn't an onion anymore. It's garlic.

96
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,310
What?

97
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:24,590
When did it get so small?

98
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:30,720
- Kwon Sang Pil. 
 - What?

99
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,720
Why aren't you dating these days?

100
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:35,030
Do you think I don't want to?

101
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:41,120
You and Kim Hye Ji ignored me when I asked for a blind date.

102
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:46,810
It's because you're too good for anyone.

103
00:10:46,810 --> 00:10:48,590
I don't care anymore.

104
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:53,510
I won't date until things become stable at the restaurant.

105
00:10:56,310 --> 00:10:58,430
Right.

106
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:04,520
What do you mean by "right"?

107
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:07,600
What is it? Are you dating these days?

108
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,140
Bring more onions.

109
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:12,870
I'll peel all of your onions today.

110
00:11:12,870 --> 00:11:17,460
Okay. Here are the onions!

111
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,560
 The customer is not answering the phone. 
   

112
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:37,440
 You'll be connected to the voicemail after the beep. 

113
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,980
He won't come to work or answer his phone.

114
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:42,410
What's he doing?

115
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:49,100
She parked here again. Here we go again!

116
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,710
Geez, you've got to be joking.

117
00:11:53,710 --> 00:11:55,190
   

118
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:02,060
Hello? Hello—

119
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,560
CEO Bae Hye Suk...

120
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:13,100
CEO Bae Hye Suk, I think I told you over 1,000 times

121
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:17,320
not to park in front of my building... Ma'am.

122
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,690
I don't think it was over 1,000 times... Sir.

123
00:12:22,690 --> 00:12:25,180
I don't think that's my point... Ma'am.

124
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:29,200
You're a CEO who works with numbers, but you're exaggerating too much.

125
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,930
I can't really trust you. Don't you think?

126
00:12:30,930 --> 00:12:34,790
- What does that have to do with— 
 - And to be accurate,

127
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:39,210
my car is parked in front of this building, not your building.

128
00:12:39,210 --> 00:12:43,400
The owner of this building allowed me to park,

129
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:46,400
unlike someone so petty.

130
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,230
"P-Petty"?

131
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:52,500
"P-Petty"? Me?

132
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,190
You've got to be fooling me.

133
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:58,010
Why does our CEO insist on parking there?

134
00:12:58,010 --> 00:13:00,110
- There are spots over here too. 
 - Further this way...

135
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:05,490
Actually, CEO had been trying to buy that building for a while.

136
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:10,760
- But three years ago, that man bought it before she could. 
 - Am I petty?

137
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,210
Once she holds on to something, she never lets go.

138
00:13:13,210 --> 00:13:15,340
I can see why she's holding grudges.

139
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:16,400
Right?

140
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,900
Is it because...

141
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:26,890
Is it because I'm your first love, and you haven't moved on?

142
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:32,450
I think you mean yourself.

143
00:13:33,410 --> 00:13:37,910
You were a loser but cute when you were young.

144
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,490
But now...

145
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:44,230
How pathetic.

146
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:48,780
Please stop acting familiar with me. It's annoying!

147
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:52,740
"P-Pathetic"? "Annoying"?

148
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:55,720
You aren't my first love, Bae Hye Suk!

149
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:59,060
And stop parking in front of my building!

150
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:01,480
See? You...

151
00:14:02,290 --> 00:14:05,450
You're a little closer to this side!

152
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:22,300
 I liked you then, and I like you now. 

153
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:26,720
 It took me too long to say that. 

154
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,600
 Are you happy? 

155
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:48,420
 Yes, I am. I feel satisfied. 

156
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:53,680
You shouldn't be acting that way now.

157
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:57,800
- Why? 
 - I tried to extend your business trip

158
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,650
using the Roem project, but HQ won't allow it.

159
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:05,480
Have you talked to your mom?

160
00:15:06,590 --> 00:15:08,920
She won't answer my calls.

161
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,590
How about you go to the States then return?

162
00:15:10,590 --> 00:15:12,780
Finish the project you were working on,

163
00:15:12,780 --> 00:15:16,050
plan for the early phase, and talk to your mom.

164
00:15:16,050 --> 00:15:21,930
Don't you think you'd get assigned back here then?

165
00:15:21,930 --> 00:15:23,490
How long would that take?

166
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:24,940
A month?

167
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:28,190
A month and a half or two months?

168
00:15:28,190 --> 00:15:29,500
That's why I don't want to.

169
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,600
Don't you want to? Then what will you do?

170
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:35,000
Will you quit your job or something?

171
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,470
There's no guarantee that things will work out with Lee Ddoong.

172
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:41,070
What's so great about a first love that you'd bet all on it?

173
00:15:41,070 --> 00:15:42,800
Did something happen to you?

174
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,210
I'm worried about you right now!

175
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:47,160
Whatever! Do whatever you want!

176
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:49,650
I won't worry about you anymore.

177
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:52,690
Be in love for 1,000 years.

178
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:55,000
 Do you think you're the only one with a first love? 

179
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,150
 I have one, too! 

180
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:59,460
What's wrong with him?

181
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,700
- Teacher Min Seok. 
 - Yes?

182
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:20,360
Did Teacher Son go to the class assembly?

183
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,940
- No, he went to the vice principal's office. 
 - Why?

184
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:26,040
He kept wanting to see Teacher Son today for some reason.

185
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,220
- Really? 
 - Yes.

186
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,490
Teacher Son!

187
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:51,220
Why was it so difficult to see you all day?

188
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,130
I've been looking for you everywhere.

189
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:55,170
I'm sorry. Well,

190
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:57,400
the vice principal wanted to see me.

191
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,000
Here's the thing.

192
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:04,000
This weekend, he wants me to—

193
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,900
- Did Dad ask you to go hiking with him again? 
 - No, it's not that.

194
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:11,300
For this weekend, he asked me to...

195
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:14,100
plan a date...

196
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:18,000
- A d-date... 
 - D-Date, what date?

197
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:24,380
He asked me to plan a hiking date with the teachers.

198
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:27,800
Isn't he sick of climbing the same mountain all the time?

199
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:34,000
He tries to do things with you every weekend since you never refuse.

200
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,290
Things are easier for me and my sister, thanks to you,

201
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:39,610
but he's taking it too far.

202
00:17:39,610 --> 00:17:42,390
You should start saying no to him.

203
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:44,000
I'll try my best.

204
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,910
Good. What are you doing tomorrow?

205
00:17:46,910 --> 00:17:48,520
- Me? 
 - Yes.

206
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:51,800
- Why do you ask? 
 - We have only four periods tomorrow.

207
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:54,840
- Let's go get something tasty. It's my treat. 
 - It's okay.

208
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:57,930
It's because I'd like to thank you. Don't feel pressured.

209
00:17:57,930 --> 00:18:01,020
I-It's nothing. I didn't do much.

210
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:02,730
You did a lot.

211
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:05,030
If it wasn't for you,

212
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:09,830
I would have been a clueless friend who interfered with my friend's relationship.

213
00:18:09,830 --> 00:18:11,820
Do you already have plans, by chance?

214
00:18:11,820 --> 00:18:14,610
No, I don't.

215
00:18:14,610 --> 00:18:18,650
Then tomorrow, your afternoon is mine.

216
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:20,690
I'm glad.

217
